{"TopicId":165605,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"orbital launch from back of a plane?","CreatedByName":"tjsnh","CreatedById":108021,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-17T16:24:57Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"tjsnh","CreatedById":108021,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-17T16:24:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSeeking advice;\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nI\u0027d like to craft a mission profile to launch an orbital vehicle from the back of an aircraft. That part isn\u0027t especially difficult. However ...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnyone know of any addons or something that can be done to prevent the plane from flying out of control and crashing while you are \u0022focused\u0022 on the orbital vehicle, and the launch plane is still in the atmosphere?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbart","CreatedById":78303,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-17T16:30:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s not even the \u0022out of control\u0022 part that is the problem. Even if you\u0027d have an autopilot (and that\u0027s a big if), the moment your aircraft is outside the \u0022physics bubble\u0022 (and with your spacecraft reaching orbital velocity, that\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Ewill\u003C/em\u003E\u00A0happen) it will cease to exist as it\u0027s inside the atmosphere on a suborbital trajectory, and that\u0027s how the game deals with such objects on rails.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spricigo","CreatedById":166502,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-17T16:31:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed1670961408\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/157214-13-flight-manager-for-reusable-stages-fmrs-now-with-recoverycontroller-integration/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:232px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"A_name","CreatedById":134040,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-18T18:35:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223174417\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022165605\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221505665901\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022166502\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Spricigo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 17/9/2017 at 11:31 AM, Spricigo said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed1107272511\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/157214-13-flight-manager-for-reusable-stages-fmrs-now-with-recoverycontroller-integration/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:214px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv title=\u0022Protected by Grammarly\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is the only real way to do it reliably.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vanamonde","CreatedById":27914,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-18T22:16:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nModding question moved to the modding subforum.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spricigo","CreatedById":166502,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-19T03:58:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223175170\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022165605\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221505759726\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022134040\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022A_name\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, A_name said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is the only real way to do it reliably.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTechnicaly one can do it in stock. \u00A0But that requires the going suborbital then release the rocket,\u00A0circularize and switch back to\u00A0the plane\u00A0before it\u00A0disappeas. In other words: cool but impractical.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"danielboro","CreatedById":166078,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-19T08:22:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nusing stage recovery you can get the $ (and parts if you use scrapyard) of the aircraft back and pretend it landed\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"A_name","CreatedById":134040,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-19T15:06:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223175469\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022165605\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221505793485\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022166502\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Spricigo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 hours ago, Spricigo said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTechnicaly one can do it in stock. \u00A0But that requires the going suborbital then release the rocket,\u00A0circularize and switch back to\u00A0the plane\u00A0before it\u00A0disappeas. In other words: cool but impractical.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut how reliable would that be, that was my point. You can definitely pull it off more often than not but it\u0027s not a solution.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spricigo","CreatedById":166502,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-19T20:40:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223175691\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022165605\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221505833583\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022134040\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022A_name\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, A_name said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut how reliable would that be, that was my point. You can definitely pull it off more often than not but it\u0027s not a solution.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd I was not disagreeing. \u003Ci\u003ETechnically\u00A0\u003C/i\u003Eit can be done in stock, but one need to design the aircraft to be almost an \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E without all the convenience of a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStill, maybe motivated by the rule of cool, that is a possibility.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ForScience6686","CreatedById":144187,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-19T22:38:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223175469\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022165605\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221505793485\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022166502\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Spricigo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n17 hours ago, Spricigo said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTechnicaly one can do it in stock. \u00A0But that requires the going suborbital then release the rocket,\u00A0circularize and switch back to\u00A0the plane\u00A0before it\u00A0disappeas. In other words: cool but impractical.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot exactly, you don\u0027t have to reach orbit, just be on a high enough sub orbital path that you can land the plane before you start coming back down.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://kerbalx.com/ForScience6686/Goose-x\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://kerbalx.com/ForScience6686/Goose-x\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spricigo","CreatedById":166502,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-20T08:49:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223176010\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022165605\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221505860707\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022144187\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ForScience6686\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 hours ago, ForScience6686 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot exactly, you don\u0027t have to reach orbit, just be on a high enough sub orbital path that you can land the plane before you start coming back down.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://kerbalx.com/ForScience6686/Goose-x\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://kerbalx.com/ForScience6686/Goose-x\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou nitpick of my nitpick is correct.\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:sticktongue:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue2.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:sticktongue:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}